#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.36:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.36:0.2"
msgid "4. Satullapakāyikavagga "
msgstr "4. The Satullapa Group "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.36:0.3"
msgid "36. Saddhāsutta "
msgstr "36. Faith "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn1.36:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.36:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā satullapakāyikā devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, several glorious deities of the Satullapa Group, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. "

msgctxt "sn1.36:1.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Standing to one side, one deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.54, sc2
msgctxt "sn1.36:2.1"
msgid "“Saddhā dutiyā purisassa hoti, "
msgstr "“Faith is a person’s partner. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:2.2"
msgid "No ce assaddhiyaṃ avatiṭṭhati; "
msgstr "If faithlessness doesn’t linger, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:2.3"
msgid "Yaso ca kittī ca tatvassa hoti, "
msgstr "fame and renown are theirs, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:2.4"
msgid "Saggañca so gacchati sarīraṃ vihāyā”ti. "
msgstr "and when they discard this corpse they go to heaven.” "

# NOTE: See https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/possible-textual-loss-in-sn-1-36/3350
#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn1.36:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho aparā devatā bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then another deity recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn1.36:4.1"
msgid "“Kodhaṃ jahe vippajaheyya mānaṃ, "
msgstr "“Give up anger, get rid of conceit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:4.2"
msgid "Saṃyojanaṃ sabbamatikkameyya; "
msgstr "and get past all the fetters. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ nāmarūpasmimasajjamānaṃ, "
msgstr "Clingings don’t torment one who has nothing, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:4.4"
msgid "Akiñcanaṃ nānupatanti saṅgā”ti. "
msgstr "not clinging to name and form.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn1.36:5.1"
msgid "“Pamādamanuyuñjanti, "
msgstr "“Fools and unintelligent people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:5.2"
msgid "bālā dummedhino janā; "
msgstr "devote themselves to negligence. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:5.3"
msgid "Appamādañca medhāvī, "
msgstr "But the intelligent protect diligence "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:5.4"
msgid "dhanaṃ seṭṭhaṃva rakkhati. "
msgstr "as their best treasure. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn1.36:6.1"
msgid "Mā pamādamanuyuñjetha, "
msgstr "Don’t devote yourself to negligence, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:6.2"
msgid "mā kāmarati santhavaṃ; "
msgstr "or delight in sexual intimacy. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:6.3"
msgid "Appamatto hi jhāyanto, "
msgstr "For if you’re diligent and practice absorption, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.36:6.4"
msgid "pappoti paramaṃ sukhan”ti. "
msgstr "you’ll attain the highest happiness.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
